ZH: 我的上级要求我加班工作。
EN: My superior asked me to work overtime.

ZH: 请向你的上级报告这个问题。
EN: Please report this issue to your supervisor.

ZH: 上级领导告诉我们要提高工作效率。
EN: The higher-ups told us to improve work efficiency.

ZH: 他的上级很严格，要求工作要做到最好。
EN: His superior is very strict and requires the work to be done perfectly.

ZH: 作为我的上级，他对我的工作质量有很高的要求。
EN: As my superior, he has high expectations for the quality of my work.

ZH: 你需要经过上级同意才能离开岗位。
EN: You need permission from your supervisor to leave your post.

ZH: 上级的指示是我们必须完成这项任务。
EN: The directive from the higher-ups is that we must complete this task.

ZH: 我的上级领导在会议上讲述了新的工作方向。
EN: My superior explained the new direction for work at the meeting.

ZH: 如果有问题，请及时向上级汇报。
EN: Please report to your superior promptly if there are any issues.

ZH: 上级给了我们很大的支持和鼓励。
EN: The higher-ups have given us great support and encouragement.

ZH: 员工应该尊重自己的上级。
EN: Employees should respect their superiors.

ZH: 我向我的上级汇报了这个项目的进展。
EN: I reported the progress of this project to my superior.

ZH: 上级希望我们能够按时完成任务。
EN: The higher-ups hope that we can complete the task on time.

ZH: 请接受我的上级的指导。
EN: Please accept the guidance of my superior.

ZH: 我的上级决定对我们进行一次培训。
EN: My superior decided to have a training session for us.

ZH: 作为员工，我们应该服从上级的安排。
EN: As employees, we should obey the arrangements of our superiors.

ZH: 上级领导对我们的工作表现进行了评估。
EN: The higher-ups evaluated our job performance.

ZH: 请向您的上级领导汇报这个问题。
EN: Please report this issue to your senior leader.

ZH: 上级的决定是最终决定，我们要遵循。
EN: The decision of the higher-ups is final and we must follow it.

ZH: 上级的建议是对我们发展非常有帮助的。
EN: The advice of the superiors is very helpful for our development.
